  "text": "The system of equations in Equation (4) is currently not unique for the four impedance parameters of x (Equation (5)). However, using the assumption of reciprocity, generally true for circuits containing passive elements only and shown to be true for the KLM model [CITATION_1] , Z 12 = Z 21 . During the calculation of the impedance parameters, the square root of Z 12 Z 21 is taken, which gives a positive real impedance value for both Z 12 and Z 21 . Since there are three unknown terms remaining in x, at any given frequency, measurements of the input impedance Z in using at least three different acoustic loads Z L allows an estimate of the parameter vector x to be obtained using matrix inversion. The equation system will have a unique solution as long as the impedance properties of the three loads are different.",
